e%20employee%2C%20whose%20identity%20Business%20Insider%20confirmed%2C%20asked%20to%20remain%20anonymous%20to%20discuss%20internal%20matters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIntel%20has%20privately%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.intel.com%2Fcontent%2Fwww%2Fus%2Fen%2Fnewsroom%2Fnews%2Fupdates-intel-10-largest-construction-projects.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einvested%20billions%20%3C%2Fa%3Ein%20factory%20expansions%20in%20New%20Mexico%2C%20Arizona%2C%20Ohio%2C%20and%20Oregon.%20It%20has%20not%20yet%20received%20the%20CHIPS%20grants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGelsinger%20publicly%20addressed%20this%20topic%20in%20a%20Thursday%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Fvideos%2F2024-10-31%2Fintel-ceo-pat-gelsinger-on-q4-forecast%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einterview%20with%20Bloomberg%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20the%20third%20quarter%20earnings%20call.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20CHIPS%20Act%20was%20a%20bipartisan%20act%2C%20and%20with%20that%20strong%20support%20from%20both%20sides%20of%20the%20aisle%2C%20we%20believe%20the%20importance%20of%20that%20in%20terms%20of%20industrial%20policy.%20The%20semiconductor%20is%20well-supported%20by%20Congress%20and%20both%20parties%2C%26quot%3B%20Gelsinger%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20addressed%20the%20delay%20of%20CHIPS%20Act%20funding%20distribution.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20disappointed%20by%20how%20long%20and%20how%20slow%20the%20dispensing%20of%20funds%20has%20been%20and%20it's%20well%20over%20two%20years%20at%20this%20point.%20I've%20invested%2030%20billion%20in%20capital%20and%20we've%20seen%20%240%20of%20the%20grants%20at%20this%20point.%20So%20we%20do%20believe%20that%20that%20has%20been%20too%20slow%2C%20and%20we're%20somewhat%20frustrated%20by%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20Gelsinger%20said%20in%20the%20Bloomberg%20interview.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPolicymakers%20recently%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20have%20discussed%20whether%20Intel%20needs%20additional%20help%20beyond%20the%20CHIPS%20Act