ise%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20last%20week%20has%20been%20all%20about%20candidates%20trying%20to%20create%20%26quot%3Bbreakthrough%20moments%26quot%3B%20to%20benefit%20their%20campaigns%2C%20leveraging%20instances%20where%20a%20candidate%20or%20someone%20associated%20with%20them%20was%20seen%20as%20demeaning%20a%20large%20swath%20of%20the%20American%20public.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20a%20lot%20of%20noise%20in%20the%20course%20of%20a%20presidential%20campaign%2C%20with%20candidates%20(and%20their%20surrogates)%20giving%20interviews%20and%20appearing%20at%20rallies%20virtually%20every%20day.%20For%20the%20average%20voter%2C%20particularly%20those%20who%20are%20less%20engaged%2C%20it's%20pretty%20easy%20to%20tune%20it%20all%20out%20%E2%80%94%20unless%20there's%20a%20moment%20when%20one%20particular%20event%20dominates%20headlines%2C%20filters%20down%20organically%20to%20social%20media%2C%20and%20spurs%20conversations%20at%20dinner%20tables.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20breakthrough%20moments%20are%20naturally%20built%20into%20the%20campaign%20schedule.%20Historically%2C%20candidates%20have%20received%20a%20%26quot%3Bconvention%20bump%26quot%3B%20in%20their%20polling%20after%20their%20respective%20nominating%20conventions%2C%20driven%20by%20the%20largely%20positive%20coverage%20that%20blankets%20TV%20networks%2C%20newspapers%2C%20and%2C%20increasingly%2C%20social%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDebates%20also%20provide%20natural%20breakthrough%20moments%2C%20with%20tens%20of%20millions%20of%20voters%20tuning%20in%20to%20watch%20the%20candidates%20face%20off.%20But%20the%20last%20debate%20was%20one%20month%20ago%2C%20and%20the%20broad%20contours%20of%20the%20race%20have%20remained%20relatively%20static%20since%20then.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20leaves%20it%20to%20each%20campaign%20to%20try%20to%20generate%20their%20own%20moments%2C%20like%20when%20Trump%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-harris-mcdonalds-fry-cook-economy-election-2024-10%5C%22