2C000.%20Almost%20a%20decade%20later%2C%20we%20realized%20that%20what%20we%20planned%20for%20wasn't%20nearly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Flife-insurance%2Fhow-much-life-insurance-do-i-need%5C%22%3Eenough%20life%20insurance%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20meet%20my%20needs%20if%20my%20husband%20were%20to%20die.%20Indeed%2C%20our%20lives%20have%20changed%20fairly%20dramatically%20since%20we%20bought%20the%20policy%20%E2%80%94%20my%20husband%20has%20become%20my%20caretaker%20due%20to%20a%20chronic%20illness%2C%20and%20he%20earns%20the%20only%20regular%20paycheck.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20%24300%2C000%20payout%20wouldn't%20last%20me%20very%20long%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20my%20husband%20died%20and%20the%20policy%20paid%20out%20in%20full%2C%20over%20half%20of%20that%20money%20would%20go%20to%20paying%20off%20the%20mortgage%20on%20our%20condo.%20Another%20big%20chunk%20would%20go%20for%20cremation%2C%20burial%2C%20and%20funeral.%20(Let's%20not%20even%20begin%20to%20talk%20about%20the%20possibility%20of%20hospital%20bills%20from%20a%20lengthy%20illness.)%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlso%2C%20if%20there%20were%20no%20other%20outstanding%20bills%2C%20I%20would%20be%20responsible%20for%20homeowner's%20insurance%2C%20HOA%20fees%2C%20health%20insurance%20%E2%80%94%20and%20with%20just%20those%20three%20bills%2C%20the%20money%20left%20over%20from%20the%20other%20expenses%20wouldn't%20last%20me%2010%20years.%20If%20we%20throw%20in%20groceries%2C%20internet%2C%20transportation%2C%20medications%2C%20etc.%2C%20the%20money%20would%20be%20gone%20in%20less%20than%20five.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGet%20Life%20Insurance%20Quotes%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompare%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Flife-insurance%2Fbest-cheap-life-insurance%5C%22%3Eaffordable%20life%20insurance%3C%2Fa%3E%20options%20with%20Policygenius.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Faside%3E%3Ch2%3EGetting%20a%20new%20policy%20isn't%20easy%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20outbreak%20of%20COVID-19%2C%20we%20have%20been%20thinking%20way%20more%20about%20our%20mortality.%20My%20husband%20has%20an%20autoimmune%20disease%20and%20is%20at%20risk%20for%20complications%20due%20to%20the%20virus.%20Living%20during%20a%20global%20pandemic%20was%20a%20particularly%20scary%20time%2C%20and%20finances%20and%20the%20future%20seemed%20to%20be%20on%20everyone's%20mind.%20I%20know%20they%20were%20on%20ours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20problem%20of%20not%20having%20enough%20life%20insurance%20seems%20easy%20enough%20to%20fix%20%E2%80%94%20just%20buy%20more.%20But%20we%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbanking%2Fhow-to-budget%5C%22%3Elive%20on%20a%20budget%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20we're%20both%20over%2050%2C%20so%20buying%20a%20new%20policy%20is%20cost-prohibitive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnfortunately%2C%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20waited%20to%20get%20life%20insurance%20until%20we%20were%20in%20our%2040s%2C%20when%20it%20was%20already%20more%20expensive%20than%20if%20we%20had%20purchased%20it%20a%20decade%20earlier.%20We%20believed%20that%20covering%20the%20mortgage%20and%20the%20death%20expenses%20would%20be%20enough%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20I%20was%20secure%20in%20life%20without%20his%20paycheck.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWe%20wish%20we'd%20bought%20more%20insurance%20when%20we%20were%20younger%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20this%20point%2C%20we%20wish%20we%20had%20gone%20with%20a%20much%20bigger%20policy%20payout.%20Even%20%24500%2C000%20would%20put%20me%20in%20a%20much%20better%20position%20if%20something%20happened%20to%20my%20husband.%20Of%20course%2C%20a%20%241%20million%20policy%2C%20although%20it%20sounds%20so%20high%2C%20would%20leave%20me%20in%20a%20place%20to%20not%20have%20to%20worry%20about%20money%20or%20finances%20at%20all.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20know%20it%20seems%20counterintuitive%20to%20say%20that%20young%20people%20should%20buy%20larger%20life%20insurance%20policies%2C%20but%20if%