nd%20that%20mark%20as%20well.%20Inflation%20runs%20about%208%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVTB%20said%20the%20borrowers%20could%20take%20loans%20of%20up%20to%206%20million%20rubles%2C%20or%20roughly%20%2461%2C000.%20Average%20salaries%20in%20Russia%20are%20around%20%2410%2C000%20a%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVTB%20is%20mostly%20owned%20by%20the%20Russian%20state%2C%20and%20while%20it%20didn't%20give%20a%20reason%20for%20the%20low%20rate%2C%20it%20aligns%20with%20other%20Russian%20efforts%20to%20cement%20its%20hold%20on%20occupied%20land.%20It%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%20claimed%20the%20two%20territories%20as%20its%20own%20in%20a%20September%202022%20annexation%2C%20even%20as%20some%20parts%20of%20them%20remained%20in%20Ukraine's%20hands%20or%20on%20the%20front%20lines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%2C%20NATO%2C%20and%20Ukraine's%20allies%20have%20long%20called%20on%20Russia%20to%20withdraw%20from%20the%20territory%20and%20return%20it%20to%20Ukraine%2C%20which%20continues%20to%20fight%20for%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20return%20gets%20harder%20if%20more%20and%20more%20Russians%20move%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAgathe%20Demarais%2C%20a%20senior%20policy%20fellow%20on%20geoeconomics%20at%20the%20European%20Council%20on%20Foreign%20Relations%2C%20saw%20the%20low%20rate%20as%20a%20clear%20incentive%20for%20Russians%20in%20the%20area%20to%20stay%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20aim%20is%20to%20consolidate%20Russia's%20long-term%20presence%20%E2%80%94%20through%2030-year%20loans%2C%20which%20is%20highly%20unusual%20in%20Russia%20%E2%80%94%20in%20the%20occupied%20Ukrainian%20regions%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20moves%20by%20Russian%20to%20tighten%20its%20grip%20include%20implementing%20a%20Russian%20curriculum%20in%20schools%2C%20including%20a%20pro-Russian%20view%20of%20history.%20It%20also%20made%20the%20ruble%20the%20official%20currency%2C%20supplanting%20the%20Ukrainian%20hryvnia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsprotyv.mod.gov.ua%2Fen%2Fputin-plans-to-populate-the-temporarily-occupied-territories-of-ukraine-with-trustworthy-people%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esays%3C%2Fa%3E%20Russia%20has%20offered%20financial%20incentives%2C%20up%20to%205%20million%20rubles%20or%20%2451%2C000%2C%20to%20Russians%20who%20move%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2201b6d241-170d-4650-8c0c-8039c44dafce%5C%22%3EA%20topsy-turvy%20housing%20market%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2024-07-01%2Frussia-ends-housing-mortgage-subsidy-that-stoked-a-property-boom%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehas%20subsidized%20mortgages%20by%20offering%20attractive%20rates%20before%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20though%20to%20a%20lesser%20extent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20did%20so%20near%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20and%20then%20to%20counter%20the%20sanctions%20piled%20on%20it%20by%20Western%20nations%20after%20the%202022%20invasion%2C%20capping%20them%20at%208%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20house%20prices%20soared%20in%20response%20and%20Russia%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.themoscowtimes.com%2F2024%2F10%2F18%2Frussias-real-estate-market-rocked-by-the-end-of-generous-mortgage-subsidies-a86738%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epulled%20the%20broad%20subsidy%20in%20July%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20rate%20for%20the%20occupied%20regions%20offers%20Russians%20far%20better%20terms%20than%20even%20the%20earlier%20subsidy%20%E2%80%94%20but%20with%20the%20significant%20catch%20of%20living%20close%20to%20the%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224fd3d16d-28af-4c7e-aa32-4bc88a198c7b%5C%22%3EFierce%20fighting%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERussian%20troops%20are%20trying%20to%20capture%20the%20remainder%20of%20Luhansk%20and%20Donetsk%2C%20which%20Ukraine%20still%20holds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20territories%20had%20long%20been%20relatively%20static%2C%20though%20h